  "response": "Yahoo Fantasy Hockey follows standard fantasy hockey rules, but here are some key points:\n\n1. League Setup:\n- Typically 12 teams\n- Draft or auction to select players\n- Can be head-to-head or rotisserie scoring\n\n2. Roster Composition:\n- Usually includes forwards, defensemen, and goalies\n- Specific positions like center, left wing, right wing\n- Bench and IR spots\n\n3. Scoring:\n- Can be standard or custom scoring\n- Categories often include goals, assists, plus/minus, penalty minutes\n- Goalie stats like wins, saves, goals against average\n\n4. Gameplay:\n- Head-to-head leagues compete weekly against another team\n- Rotisserie leagues accumulate stats throughout the season\n- Weekly roster management and lineup changes\n- Free agent/waiver wire pickups\n- Trades between teams\n\n5. Draft Types:\n- Snake draft\n- Auction draft\n- Auto draft\n\n6. League Settings:\n- Commissioners can customize many rules\n- Can set draft date, scoring, roster limits\n\nSpecific details can vary depending on the specific league settings, so it's best to check the exact rules of your particular Yahoo Fantasy Hockey league.",
